ker_005\n- docker_006\n- docker_007\n- docker_008\n\n(if the root cause is at the service level, i.e., if all pods of a specific service are faulty, the root cause is the service itself)\n\n- db_001\n- db_002\n- db_003\n- db_004\n- db_005\n- db_006\n- db_007\n- db_008\n- db_009\n- db_010\n- db_011\n- db_012\n- db_013\n\nAnomaly Cluster Description:\nAt exactly 00:01:00, we detected 22 simultaneous trace duration anomalies across multiple entities. The OSB service (os_021) showed abnormal duration at the root level, while docker containers 001-004 and 008 experienced prolonged calls to CSF, RemoteProcess, JDBC, and LOCAL methods (especially db_009 methods). docker_003 had 7 abnormal LOCAL methods on db_009. This suggests a system-wide latency event affecting inter-service communication.\n\nRelevant Historical Incidents (if any):\n[Past Incident 1] (Score: 0.494)\nComponent: os_021 | Metrics: connection, latency, network, rr, rt, sr\nSummary: Component: os_021\nEvent: os_021 failure at 2020-05-23 01:16:00\nSystem Type: Banking Microservice (node)\nSymptoms: network loss; The node identified as the ground truth root cause, `os_021`, exhibited an anomaly in `tnsping_result_time` starting at 01:18:00. This metric directly measures network connectivity health to a databas; Coinciding with the failure timestamp of 01:16:00, database `db_011` began reporting anomalies for `rejected_connections`, providing direct evidence that clients were unable to establish connections.; Immediately following the initial failure, application containers like `docker_001` and `docker_006` showed increased `DbTime` starting at 01:17:00, a classic symptom of database communication latency\nAffected Metrics: connection, latency, network, rr, rt, sr\nRoot Cause Category: The root cause of the incident was a network loss on the node `os_021`, which occurred at 2020-05-23 01:16:00 UTC+8. This network failure disrupted co\nFailure Pattern: The root cause of the incident was a network loss on the node `os_021`, which occurred at 2020-05-23 01:16:00 UTC+8. This network failure disrupted communication between services and databases, leading to widespread connectivity issues and cascading failures across the system.\nMitigation Principles: Implement more robust network monitoring on all nodes, specifically focusing on packet loss, latency, and active connectivity checks between critical components (e.g., application nodes to database nodes). Enhance alerting for metrics like `tnsping_result_time` to provide earlier warnings of network degradation. Review and improve application-level retry logic and circuit-breaking patterns to handle transient network failures more gracefully.\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
